1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:06,172
[brazen music playing]

2
00:00:09,801 --> 00:00:14,681
[electronic blipping]

3
00:00:18,143 --> 00:00:20,437
[Paldo] <i>Sir, I think</i>
<i>you killed Atoy's father.</i>

4
00:00:20,520 --> 00:00:21,730
[Red] <i>Serves him right.</i>

5
00:00:21,813 --> 00:00:23,231
<i>His life is the price</i>
<i>for his son's mistakes.</i>

6
00:00:23,314 --> 00:00:27,902
You'll finally look your best when you
meet Saint Peter and Mom in heaven.

7
00:00:28,486 --> 00:00:30,780
[in English] Have you thought
of your next plan, Captain?

8
00:00:30,864 --> 00:00:32,198
Are you really going back to work?

9
00:00:32,282 --> 00:00:35,118
[Atoy] <i>It has always been my dad's dream</i>
<i>for me to inherit this.</i>

10
00:00:35,660 --> 00:00:38,663
[Cita] <i>Where on earth is Karla?</i>
<i>She was told to come and help.</i>

11
00:00:38,747 --> 00:00:40,331
[Atoy] <i>She's probably still</i>
<i>out there skateboarding.</i>

12
00:00:40,415 --> 00:00:41,166
‪[clamoring]

13
00:00:41,249 --> 00:00:43,752
[Karla] <i>I'm really sorry! There's</i>
<i>something wrong with my skateboard!</i>

14
00:00:43,835 --> 00:00:44,711
- [screams]
- [Emerson groans]

15
00:00:44,794 --> 00:00:46,463
[Atoy] <i>What's gotten into you? You're</i>
<i>getting more immature as you get older!</i>

16
00:00:46,546 --> 00:00:49,048
Come with me. I've got a gig for you.

17
00:00:49,132 --> 00:00:50,508
[Karla] Please buy us some drinks.

18
00:00:50,592 --> 00:00:52,135
Wait, I don't think I have any change.

19
00:00:52,218 --> 00:00:54,679
- [Ibyang] <i>Cash transfer will do.</i>
- [Karla] <i>My cell phone!</i>

20
00:00:54,763 --> 00:00:56,806
- [Ibyang] <i>I'm calling the police!</i>
- [Atoy] <i>Are you the snatcher?</i>

21
00:00:56,890 --> 00:00:59,059
You're actually good-looking,
but it's a shame you're so judgmental!

22
00:00:59,142 --> 00:01:00,810
They actually let you off the hook?

23
00:01:00,894 --> 00:01:02,854
Of course! After all, I'm a great actress.

24
00:01:02,937 --> 00:01:04,606
I knew you were lying.

25
00:01:04,689 --> 00:01:08,651
I'm going to drop this
if you don't give us the phone back.

26
00:01:08,735 --> 00:01:09,944
Really now?

27
00:01:10,028 --> 00:01:12,530
[Atoy] <i>She may look nice,</i>
<i>but she turned out to be a thief.</i>

28
00:01:12,614 --> 00:01:15,283
I'll head over to Sir John's shop for now.

29
00:01:15,366 --> 00:01:17,118
[Ame] <i>I'll also sell the phone, okay?</i>

30
00:01:17,202 --> 00:01:18,578
For your next mission,

31
00:01:19,662 --> 00:01:22,248
our VIP client is ordering you
to track him down.

32
00:01:22,957 --> 00:01:26,294
I hear he’s a six-time champion
in big-time cockfights.

33
00:01:26,377 --> 00:01:27,712
Even if it means squeezing
through the eye of a needle,

34
00:01:28,296 --> 00:01:30,757
- You'll go through it, just to find him.
- I'll go through it, just to find him.

35
00:01:30,840 --> 00:01:33,802
I know a gig. It pays 1,000 a night.

36
00:01:33,885 --> 00:01:35,553
I really don't want it!

37
00:01:35,637 --> 00:01:39,182
- [brazen music continues]
- [dog barking in distance]

38
00:01:39,265 --> 00:01:42,018
[muffled grunting]

39
00:01:45,063 --> 00:01:46,689
Spicy and sour.

40
00:01:48,900 --> 00:01:51,236
That'll do. Thank you, thank you.

41
00:01:51,319 --> 00:01:52,153
[Atoy] Thank you.

42
00:01:52,946 --> 00:01:54,864
Hey! Sorry, sorry, sorry.

43
00:01:54,948 --> 00:01:59,410
[suspicious music playing]

44
00:02:00,578 --> 00:02:01,704
Miss, I'd like one more.

45
00:02:11,923 --> 00:02:12,757
‪[birds chirping]

46
00:02:19,055 --> 00:02:20,265
Ame?

47
00:02:20,974 --> 00:02:25,562
[somber music playing]

48
00:02:27,147 --> 00:02:28,481
[Ibyang] Ame?

49
00:02:36,030 --> 00:02:37,157
Ame?

50
00:02:41,369 --> 00:02:42,620
Ame?

51
00:02:45,498 --> 00:02:46,875
Ame!

52
00:02:49,085 --> 00:02:50,461
Ame!

53
00:02:50,545 --> 00:02:52,338
[somber music continues]

54
00:02:54,090 --> 00:02:55,300
‪[indistinct chattering]

55
00:02:56,551 --> 00:02:59,220
[Ibyang] Hello. Um,
have you seen my sister?

56
00:03:00,972 --> 00:03:02,140
Let me take a look at that.

57
00:03:03,600 --> 00:03:06,936
No, we haven't seen her.

58
00:03:07,645 --> 00:03:08,813
I see.

59
00:03:08,897 --> 00:03:11,107
[woman] I feel sorry for the poor child.

60
00:03:11,190 --> 00:03:13,776
[indistinct chattering]

61
00:03:13,860 --> 00:03:15,737
Maybe we should take her
to the police or the DSWD.

62
00:03:17,488 --> 00:03:20,867
Miss, have you seen my sister?

63
00:03:20,950 --> 00:03:23,369
I haven't see her around, sweetheart.

64
00:03:23,453 --> 00:03:25,288
- [indistinct chattering]
- [mutters]

65
00:03:25,371 --> 00:03:29,542
[somber music continues]

66
00:03:35,965 --> 00:03:37,467
[woman 3] Can I have this?

67
00:03:38,134 --> 00:03:40,511
Hey! You better pay for that!
The nerve of this kid!

68
00:03:45,183 --> 00:03:46,935
FATHER'S LANE
FOOD HUB IN BACLARAN

69
00:03:47,018 --> 00:03:50,396
[suave music playing]

70
00:03:50,480 --> 00:03:51,606
[swishing]

71
00:03:54,734 --> 00:03:56,736
[sewing machine whirring]

72
00:03:57,528 --> 00:03:58,988
[swishing]

73
00:03:59,072 --> 00:04:00,949
[snipping]

74
00:04:04,160 --> 00:04:05,578
[sewing machine whirring]

75
00:04:07,163 --> 00:04:08,539
[sewing machine whirring]

76
00:04:08,623 --> 00:04:09,624
[gun cocks]

77
00:04:12,210 --> 00:04:14,212
[gun firing]

78
00:04:16,589 --> 00:04:18,675
[snips]

79
00:04:28,601 --> 00:04:30,561
That kid is unbelievable.

80
00:04:32,188 --> 00:04:33,690
I’ll make you pay the moment I find you.

81
00:04:35,441 --> 00:04:36,484
My goodness.

82
00:04:37,443 --> 00:04:39,153
You will not get away with this next time.

83
00:04:39,946 --> 00:04:44,951
[pensive music playing]

84
00:04:46,202 --> 00:04:48,579
This one's for you, Ame.

85
00:04:49,872 --> 00:04:51,291
Where are you now?

86
00:04:55,837 --> 00:04:57,839
It's time for us to eat.

87
00:04:59,757 --> 00:05:00,591
[clacks]

88
00:05:00,675 --> 00:05:02,802
[pensive music continues]

89
00:05:02,885 --> 00:05:07,390
[Ibyang sobbing]

90
00:05:08,099 --> 00:05:09,309
Hey, kid.

91
00:05:10,518 --> 00:05:11,352
[Ibyang] Mmm.

92
00:05:11,436 --> 00:05:14,188
Hey, kid. What's up? What's wrong?

93
00:05:15,189 --> 00:05:18,026
My sister has gone missing.

94
00:05:18,901 --> 00:05:20,987
Well, where did you last see her?

95
00:05:21,070 --> 00:05:22,155
We should start retracing your footsteps.

96
00:05:22,238 --> 00:05:23,740
Your sister could be waiting
for you there.

97
00:05:24,365 --> 00:05:27,702
I've been looking for her all morning.

98
00:05:27,785 --> 00:05:30,580
[sobbing] She's really missing.

99
00:05:30,663 --> 00:05:33,750
She's not even at the place
she said she was going.

100
00:05:34,584 --> 00:05:39,338
I don't know where else
to look for her anymore.

101
00:05:39,422 --> 00:05:41,924
- Oh, no. [clicks tongue]
- [Ibyang sobs]

102
00:05:42,550 --> 00:05:43,593
You know, kid,

103
00:05:43,676 --> 00:05:48,931
I know someone who's really good
at finding missing people.

104
00:05:49,015 --> 00:05:51,350
Come with me. He'll help you out.

105
00:05:51,851 --> 00:05:55,229
Will he be able to find my sister, Ame?

106
00:05:55,313 --> 00:05:57,231
Definitely. It's what he does best.

107
00:05:58,066 --> 00:05:59,108
[sobs]

108
00:05:59,192 --> 00:06:02,528
- Who exactly is this person?
- [mid-tempo music playing]

109
00:06:03,029 --> 00:06:05,948
They call him the Master Cutter.

110
00:06:06,032 --> 00:06:08,076
Come with me. I'll introduce you to him.

111
00:06:08,159 --> 00:06:10,203
- Let's go.
- Okay.

112
00:06:10,286 --> 00:06:12,747
- [Cita] Easy, easy. Slowly.
- [Ibyang groans]

113
00:06:12,830 --> 00:06:14,415
I thought this was my final fitting day.

114
00:06:14,499 --> 00:06:16,876
Why does this still not fit me?

115
00:06:16,959 --> 00:06:20,004
Sir, we still need to make
some significant adjustments.

116
00:06:20,088 --> 00:06:21,214
[in English] Adjustments?

117
00:06:21,297 --> 00:06:23,049
I've been coming back
for adjustments over and over again!

118
00:06:23,132 --> 00:06:25,843
Back and forth, yet nothing ever changes.

119
00:06:25,927 --> 00:06:28,513
My time is valuable, you know.
When will this be done and over with?

120
00:06:29,138 --> 00:06:33,059
Sir, I can't help it if you
keep eating unlimited rice.

121
00:06:33,142 --> 00:06:34,060
What did you just say?

122
00:06:34,727 --> 00:06:39,023
[brazen music playing]

123
00:06:41,317 --> 00:06:42,693
When is my fitting schedule?

124
00:06:43,945 --> 00:06:46,697
Cita will notify you once
an appointment slot becomes available.

125
00:06:47,198 --> 00:06:48,282
Oh, no.

126
00:06:49,033 --> 00:06:53,371
[brazen music continues]

127
00:07:19,021 --> 00:07:21,774
Why does Mr. Altarez seem so upset?

128
00:07:21,858 --> 00:07:23,901
Oh, dear, maybe he just needs
more exercise

129
00:07:23,985 --> 00:07:25,361
and a boost of happy hormones.

130
00:07:25,445 --> 00:07:27,155
Ah.

131
00:07:27,238 --> 00:07:28,698
I have someone with me.

132
00:07:28,781 --> 00:07:30,783
A special client just for you.

133
00:07:30,867 --> 00:07:35,037
[mischievous music playing]

134
00:07:38,749 --> 00:07:40,460
- You?!
- [inaudible] Goodness.

135
00:07:44,380 --> 00:07:47,133
I don't make gowns
for flower girls, all right?

136
00:07:47,216 --> 00:07:49,802
If that's what you're looking for,
then go bother Emerson.

137
00:07:49,886 --> 00:07:51,637
I can't help you out here. Now leave.

138
00:07:52,763 --> 00:07:54,932
That's not what I'm here for.

139
00:07:55,683 --> 00:07:58,728
Miss Cita said you could help me.

140
00:07:59,312 --> 00:08:01,397
What is she even doing?

141
00:08:01,481 --> 00:08:04,025
That girl's a scammer. She's a thief.

142
00:08:04,108 --> 00:08:05,151
You're a thief?

143
00:08:05,234 --> 00:08:07,028
Yes, she is.

144
00:08:07,862 --> 00:08:09,030
Go on, get out of here.

145
00:08:09,113 --> 00:08:11,657
Please get her out of here.
Make sure she never returns again.

146
00:08:12,825 --> 00:08:16,037
But, Atoy, Ibyang's sister is missing.

147
00:08:16,120 --> 00:08:17,830
You have to help her.
I feel sorry for her.

148
00:08:18,456 --> 00:08:23,211
I'm begging you.
Please help me find my sister, Ame.

149
00:08:23,794 --> 00:08:24,962
Ame?

150
00:08:25,046 --> 00:08:25,922
Forget it.

151
00:08:26,005 --> 00:08:28,132
I bet she’s in police custody.

152
00:08:28,758 --> 00:08:31,385
Or the people you tricked
took her somewhere.

153
00:08:31,469 --> 00:08:32,929
Or she’s already been beaten up.

154
00:08:33,012 --> 00:08:36,974
I've already asked around
in three barangays,

155
00:08:37,058 --> 00:08:38,392
but still nothing.

156
00:08:40,228 --> 00:08:41,145
[whimpers]

157
00:08:41,229 --> 00:08:42,647
[Ibyang] I'm willing to pay you.

158
00:08:42,730 --> 00:08:43,814
[somber music playing]

159
00:08:43,898 --> 00:08:47,026
Here, take this as a collateral.

160
00:08:48,277 --> 00:08:49,820
How much do you charge?

161
00:08:50,530 --> 00:08:52,949
If it's expensive,
I'll pay in installments.

162
00:08:53,032 --> 00:08:56,160
[somber music continues]

163
00:08:56,244 --> 00:08:57,203
[Cita clicks tongue]

164
00:08:58,412 --> 00:09:00,289
No can do.

165
00:09:00,790 --> 00:09:03,292
You're really persistent, aren't you?
No means no. I cannot take… [stammers]

166
00:09:03,376 --> 00:09:06,087
I don't need that.
Anyway, just leave already.

167
00:09:06,170 --> 00:09:09,340
I really can't help you.
I still have other things I need to find.

168
00:09:09,423 --> 00:09:10,466
‪[dramatic musical bangs]

169
00:09:15,179 --> 00:09:19,642
You're willing to look for a chicken,
but not my sister?

170
00:09:19,725 --> 00:09:20,851
Are you for real?

171
00:09:24,272 --> 00:09:29,193
Please get that child out of here.

172
00:09:29,277 --> 00:09:31,862
[pensive music playing]

173
00:09:31,946 --> 00:09:33,906
Come on, let's go. Come on.

174
00:09:35,491 --> 00:09:38,786
I thought he was kind
and good at what he does,

175
00:09:38,869 --> 00:09:40,580
but he couldn't even bother to help me.

176
00:09:41,539 --> 00:09:44,959
Don't worry. I'll still convince him.

177
00:09:45,042 --> 00:09:47,378
He's just dealing
with something important at the moment.

178
00:09:47,461 --> 00:09:48,963
He's so grumpy.

179
00:09:49,046 --> 00:09:51,841
What is he, an old bachelor?

180
00:09:52,633 --> 00:09:54,218
I know, he really is that grumpy.

181
00:09:54,802 --> 00:09:56,596
I just don't like dealing
with stubborn people.

182
00:09:56,679 --> 00:09:57,513
- [funky music playing]
- Come on.

183
00:09:58,973 --> 00:10:00,891
Miss Cita, I can't believe he heard me.

184
00:10:00,975 --> 00:10:02,226
[Cita chuckles]

185
00:10:03,311 --> 00:10:05,521
[sighs] Oh, dear. What do we do now?

186
00:10:06,314 --> 00:10:08,357
He still refuses to help me.

187
00:10:08,941 --> 00:10:12,153
Master Cutter? More like Mister Grumpy.

188
00:10:12,236 --> 00:10:14,655
Mmm, keep it down.

189
00:10:14,739 --> 00:10:16,073
- [playful music playing]
- [chuckles]

190
00:10:16,157 --> 00:10:17,575
- Miss Cita.
- [Cita] Yes?

191
00:10:17,658 --> 00:10:20,036
We need a gown. It's for our debut.

192
00:10:20,119 --> 00:10:21,454
Sure thing. Just give me a moment.

193
00:10:21,537 --> 00:10:23,080
I'll take care of them first, okay?

194
00:10:23,164 --> 00:10:24,749
- Okay, okay.
- Come in, come in.

195
00:10:25,333 --> 00:10:26,292
[Cita] Here.

196
00:10:28,044 --> 00:10:32,506
[playful music continues]

197
00:10:41,974 --> 00:10:42,808
‪[music concludes]

198
00:10:45,019 --> 00:10:46,020
Eight.

199
00:10:46,103 --> 00:10:49,023
Putoy, are you carrying rocks
on your back,

200
00:10:49,106 --> 00:10:50,441
or do you intend to carry
the weight of the whole world?

201
00:10:50,524 --> 00:10:51,692
[clicks tongue] Straight ahead.

202
00:10:52,234 --> 00:10:53,402
There we go.

203
00:10:54,528 --> 00:10:56,280
[in English] 17.5, shoulder.

204
00:10:58,199 --> 00:11:00,117
[chimes]

205
00:11:00,201 --> 00:11:01,160
[mutters]

206
00:11:01,243 --> 00:11:05,790
[mischievous music playing]

207
00:11:06,457 --> 00:11:08,334
I think it's not accurate.

208
00:11:09,585 --> 00:11:12,213
- [in English] Twenty, arms.
- [in English] Twenty, arms.

209
00:11:12,296 --> 00:11:15,383
[mischievous music continues]

210
00:11:15,466 --> 00:11:16,425
[chimes]

211
00:11:19,845 --> 00:11:20,888
Is there a ghost here, Atoy?

212
00:11:22,640 --> 00:11:24,350
[in English] Arm hole, 20.

213
00:11:24,433 --> 00:11:25,810
[Cita, in English] Arm hole, 20.

214
00:11:25,893 --> 00:11:29,939
[mischievous music playing]

215
00:11:34,485 --> 00:11:36,987
Son of a thread.

216
00:11:38,697 --> 00:11:41,784
[brazen music playing]

217
00:11:48,249 --> 00:11:50,918
Hey, kid. Where are you headed?

218
00:11:51,001 --> 00:11:53,379
Are you going to Atoy’s
to have a gown made?

219
00:11:53,462 --> 00:11:56,382
You can come to me instead.
I can do it for less.

220
00:11:56,465 --> 00:11:58,968
- Ah… No.
- You don't need a gown?

221
00:11:59,051 --> 00:12:00,719
So, what is it then? A bedsheet?

222
00:12:00,803 --> 00:12:02,972
A pillowcase? Curtains?
Whatever it is, I can make it.

223
00:12:03,055 --> 00:12:05,015
- Oh.
- What exactly do you want?

224
00:12:05,850 --> 00:12:06,892
- [Atoy] Hey!
- [Emerson] You name it.

225
00:12:06,976 --> 00:12:09,353
- Kid, you better bring that back!
- I've got you covered.

226
00:12:09,437 --> 00:12:10,604
Wait, hold on.

227
00:12:10,688 --> 00:12:12,148
- Hey! Atoy, not so fast.
- [Atoy] Get out of my…

228
00:12:12,231 --> 00:12:13,899
- Why are you running after the poor child?
- Don't stop me. I'm in a hurry.

229
00:12:13,983 --> 00:12:14,817
Cut it out. That's enough.

230
00:12:14,900 --> 00:12:15,943
- What did the child even do to you?
- [Atoy] I'm in a hurry!

231
00:12:16,026 --> 00:12:18,112
[brazen music playing]

232
00:12:18,195 --> 00:12:20,114
[Emerson] I'm not done…
Atoy, I'm not done talking to…

233
00:12:20,197 --> 00:12:21,031
Hey!

234
00:12:21,115 --> 00:12:22,783
[upbeat brazen music continues]

235
00:12:22,867 --> 00:12:23,784
Oh, no.

236
00:12:25,453 --> 00:12:26,370
Atoy!

237
00:12:28,122 --> 00:12:30,541
I can't believe you just wrinkled it.

238
00:12:30,624 --> 00:12:34,462
[exhilarating brazen music playing]

239
00:12:45,764 --> 00:12:47,349
- [in English] Yes!
- [Atoy] Psst!

240
00:12:48,267 --> 00:12:50,102
[squeals]

241
00:12:50,186 --> 00:12:52,104
- [mischievous music playing]
- What's your problem?

242
00:12:52,188 --> 00:12:53,772
Quit screaming like something serious
is happening to you.

243
00:12:53,856 --> 00:12:55,232
I can't believe you teleported.

244
00:12:55,316 --> 00:12:57,443
- Mmm.
- It's like you're a magician or something.

245
00:12:57,526 --> 00:12:58,903
You were literally just there
a second ago.

246
00:12:58,986 --> 00:13:01,614
What did you expect? This is my hometown.

247
00:13:01,697 --> 00:13:04,492
I know every corner, every alley,
every hidden spot in this place.

248
00:13:04,575 --> 00:13:06,285
Give me what you took. Hand it over now.

249
00:13:06,368 --> 00:13:07,912
It's important to me. Give it back.

250
00:13:08,662 --> 00:13:10,539
- [Atoy] Hey.
- Oh, no!

251
00:13:10,623 --> 00:13:11,707
Come on.

252
00:13:11,790 --> 00:13:15,002
[funky music playing]

253
00:13:15,085 --> 00:13:17,630
I'm not letting you fool me this time.

254
00:13:17,713 --> 00:13:18,589
Hey.

255
00:13:19,340 --> 00:13:20,424
Hey! Get back here.

256
00:13:20,508 --> 00:13:22,301
I'll send you right back
to your mother's womb.

257
00:13:22,384 --> 00:13:25,971
[funky music continues]

258
00:13:36,190 --> 00:13:40,444
[funky music continues]

259
00:13:54,166 --> 00:13:57,378
[panting]

260
00:13:57,461 --> 00:14:01,882
[exciting music playing]

261
00:14:02,758 --> 00:14:07,680
[indistinct chattering]

262
00:14:08,347 --> 00:14:10,558
[panting]

263
00:14:13,852 --> 00:14:17,815
- [funky music playing]
- [indistinct chattering]

264
00:14:18,691 --> 00:14:22,319
[phone ringing]

265
00:14:22,403 --> 00:14:26,782
The child you brought here
stole something from me.

266
00:14:26,866 --> 00:14:28,367
I'm still running after her.

267
00:14:31,912 --> 00:14:32,913
I have to go.

268
00:14:34,290 --> 00:14:35,207
[worker 1] Careful now.

269
00:14:35,291 --> 00:14:37,251
[worker 2] Easy, easy.

270
00:14:37,334 --> 00:14:38,836
[funky music continues]

271
00:14:38,919 --> 00:14:41,046
[worker 1] Hey, hey. Slow down, okay?

272
00:14:43,424 --> 00:14:45,050
[worker 1] Slow down.

273
00:14:45,134 --> 00:14:48,345
[carpenters exclaiming]

274
00:14:48,429 --> 00:14:51,515
- Atoy, move aside!
- [exclaiming]

275
00:14:51,599 --> 00:14:53,392
- [clinking]
- [thuds]

276
00:14:57,187 --> 00:14:58,814
Hey! You almost caused an accident.

277
00:14:58,898 --> 00:15:01,609
[gentle music playing]

278
00:15:04,111 --> 00:15:04,987
- [carpenter] Sir, I'm sorry about that.
- [Atoy] It's all right, sir.

279
00:15:05,070 --> 00:15:07,948
- Stay safe.
- [carpenter] Yes, sir. Thank you so much.

280
00:15:08,032 --> 00:15:09,450
[Ibyang] Hey, hey, hey, hey.

281
00:15:09,533 --> 00:15:12,411
Please don't be mad at me anymore.
I saved you, remember?

282
00:15:13,537 --> 00:15:15,497
You're actually a good kid after all.

283
00:15:16,832 --> 00:15:18,167
Ibyang, right?

284
00:15:18,250 --> 00:15:20,502
I owe you one. I can't believe
you ended up being my hero.

285
00:15:21,086 --> 00:15:23,756
Huh. Can I at least show my gratitude?

286
00:15:24,757 --> 00:15:26,759
Can I at least give you a thank you hug?

287
00:15:27,551 --> 00:15:28,969
Not in this lifetime!

288
00:15:30,471 --> 00:15:31,388
You little…

289
00:15:31,472 --> 00:15:32,806
[brazen music playing]

290
00:15:33,390 --> 00:15:36,060
[man] Is there anything useful in here?

291
00:15:39,021 --> 00:15:42,316
Oh. We finally made it home.

292
00:15:43,734 --> 00:15:46,362
[Ibyang] Your grumpy boss
really made me run so fast.

293
00:15:47,821 --> 00:15:48,948
Goodness.

294
00:15:49,031 --> 00:15:50,991
- [man] Whoa.
- Hah!

295
00:15:51,575 --> 00:15:54,203
Oh, no! My goodness. He's still after me.

296
00:15:55,537 --> 00:15:57,998
- Help! Help me!
- [man] Ibyang?

297
00:16:00,542 --> 00:16:02,753
What's wrong, Ibyang?
What did this guy do to you?

298
00:16:02,836 --> 00:16:06,757
He's trying to abduct me.
Please get him away from me!

299
00:16:08,133 --> 00:16:11,845
[stirring music playing]

300
00:16:11,929 --> 00:16:16,475
[brazen music playing]

301
00:16:16,558 --> 00:16:19,186
It's a good thing
you didn't fight back anymore.

302
00:16:20,229 --> 00:16:21,397
[Atoy] What for?

303
00:16:21,480 --> 00:16:23,190
I would consider that
to be a waste of time.

304
00:16:24,733 --> 00:16:26,902
Anyway, that little rat
really outsmarted me.

305
00:16:26,986 --> 00:16:29,238
You shouldn't have gone after her.

306
00:16:29,321 --> 00:16:32,825
The file she took from you
surely has a soft copy anyway.

307
00:16:32,908 --> 00:16:35,119
And as for the money,
it wasn't even that much.

308
00:16:35,703 --> 00:16:38,872
I was simply fed up with that kid.

309
00:16:38,956 --> 00:16:41,709
I just wanted to talk to her parents.

310
00:16:41,792 --> 00:16:43,961
Just give them a good talking-to.

311
00:16:44,044 --> 00:16:45,754
They're just letting their child

312
00:16:45,838 --> 00:16:48,173
roam the streets,
wandering around like that.

313
00:16:48,257 --> 00:16:50,843
It's no wonder she ended up
doing all sorts of things.

314
00:16:50,926 --> 00:16:54,722
From what I know, Ibyang is an orphan.

315
00:16:54,805 --> 00:16:56,015
Poor kid.

316
00:16:56,098 --> 00:16:58,726
Ame is all she has left, and now,
she has gone missing too.

317
00:16:58,809 --> 00:17:01,603
I feel even more sorry for Ame.
That child was just as stubborn.

318
00:17:02,354 --> 00:17:03,856
They really compliment each other.

319
00:17:03,939 --> 00:17:05,065
[chuckles]

320
00:17:05,149 --> 00:17:06,567
[Cita] You should have just let it slide.

321
00:17:06,650 --> 00:17:09,236
The child is already
so helpless and alone,

322
00:17:09,319 --> 00:17:11,822
you should have brought her here instead.

323
00:17:11,905 --> 00:17:13,574
Why would I do that?

324
00:17:13,657 --> 00:17:16,744
That would be like picking up a rock
and hitting myself with it.

325
00:17:16,827 --> 00:17:20,497
[sighs] You should've
just brought her to me.

326
00:17:20,581 --> 00:17:22,207
Now I can't help but worry about her.

327
00:17:23,000 --> 00:17:23,917
For real?

328
00:17:24,001 --> 00:17:25,252
Don't even think about her.

329
00:17:25,335 --> 00:17:28,005
She's probably with
other street kids anyway.

330
00:17:28,088 --> 00:17:30,049
They can take care of her.

331
00:17:30,132 --> 00:17:30,966
‪[somber music]

332
00:17:31,592 --> 00:17:33,135
[Cita sighs] But Atoy,

333
00:17:33,218 --> 00:17:34,928
you can't really rely on them.

334
00:17:35,012 --> 00:17:37,890
At least here,
we can look after her properly.

335
00:17:38,640 --> 00:17:40,476
Poor Ibyang.

336
00:17:42,311 --> 00:17:45,939
I wonder where she is now.
I wonder what's happening to her.

337
00:17:46,648 --> 00:17:51,028
[thunder rumbling and crashing]

338
00:17:56,950 --> 00:18:01,997
[glum music playing]

339
00:18:02,581 --> 00:18:05,000
[thunder rumbling and crashing]

340
00:18:08,962 --> 00:18:12,257
[thunder rumbling and crashing]

341
00:18:22,267 --> 00:18:24,144
[Ibyang whimpering]

342
00:18:24,228 --> 00:18:28,816
- [thunder crashing]
- [whimpering]

343
00:18:40,285 --> 00:18:42,329
[sobbing]

344
00:18:42,412 --> 00:18:45,124
[thunder crashing]

345
00:18:50,170 --> 00:18:54,299
[glum music playing]

346
00:19:04,268 --> 00:19:07,312
Don't tell me you're scared of lightning.

347
00:19:07,396 --> 00:19:08,689
No, I'm not.

348
00:19:09,481 --> 00:19:12,151
[thunder crashing]

349
00:19:13,694 --> 00:19:17,114
[glum music continues]

350
00:19:17,197 --> 00:19:21,076
You know what helps when you're scared?

351
00:19:22,619 --> 00:19:23,871
Singing a song.

352
00:19:24,955 --> 00:19:29,710
♪ <i>Clack, clack, clack, clack</i>
<i>claws tapping along</i> ♪

353
00:19:29,793 --> 00:19:32,129
♪ <i>I see a crab</i> ♪

354
00:19:32,212 --> 00:19:34,339
♪ <i>In the sea</i> ♪

355
00:19:34,423 --> 00:19:38,635
- ♪ <i>Big and delicious</i> ♪
- ♪ <i>Big and delicious</i> ♪

356
00:19:38,719 --> 00:19:42,514
- ♪ <i>Hard to catch</i> ♪
- [thunder crashing]

357
00:19:42,598 --> 00:19:45,517
- ♪ <i>Because it bites</i> ♪
- ♪ <i>Because it bites</i> ♪

358
00:19:46,560 --> 00:19:48,854
♪ <i>Clack, clack, clack, clack</i>
<i>Claws tapping along</i> ♪

359
00:19:48,937 --> 00:19:51,940
- ♪ <i>I see a crab in the sea</i> ♪
- ♪ <i>I see a crab in the sea</i> ♪

360
00:19:52,024 --> 00:19:54,193
- [thunder crashing]
- ♪ <i>Big and delicious</i> ♪

361
00:19:54,276 --> 00:19:57,905
♪ <i>Hard to catch</i> ♪

362
00:19:57,988 --> 00:20:01,658
♪ <i>Because it bites</i> ♪

363
00:20:01,742 --> 00:20:05,287
♪ <i>Clack, clack, clack, clack</i>
<i>Claws tapping along</i> ♪

364
00:20:05,370 --> 00:20:09,583
♪ <i>I see a crab in the sea</i> ♪

365
00:20:09,666 --> 00:20:13,503
♪ <i>Big and delicious</i> ♪

366
00:20:13,587 --> 00:20:16,924
♪ <i>Hard to catch</i> ♪

367
00:20:17,007 --> 00:20:20,469
♪ <i>Because it bites</i> ♪

368
00:20:20,552 --> 00:20:24,097
- [sobbing]
- [thunder crashing]

369
00:20:24,181 --> 00:20:28,560
[news intro jingle playing]

370
00:20:28,644 --> 00:20:32,314
[reporter on radio] <i>A tropical depression</i>
<i>hit Metro Manila today,</i>

371
00:20:32,397 --> 00:20:34,441
<i>bringing sudden heavy rains.</i>

372
00:20:34,524 --> 00:20:39,863
<i>It carried winds estimated</i>
<i>at 35 to 65 kilometers per hour,</i>

373
00:20:39,947 --> 00:20:42,699
<i>which worsened the effects</i>
<i>of the bad weather.</i>

374
00:20:42,783 --> 00:20:44,785
<i>Due to the sudden downpour,</i>

375
00:20:44,868 --> 00:20:48,830
<i>water levels quickly rose</i>
<i>in various parts of Manila,</i>

376
00:20:48,914 --> 00:20:52,334
<i>including España, San Felipe,</i>
<i>and Quezon Avenue.</i>

377
00:20:53,335 --> 00:20:56,421
[somber music playing]

378
00:20:59,299 --> 00:21:01,635
[thunder crashing]

379
00:21:14,022 --> 00:21:16,275
[rain splattering]

380
00:21:16,358 --> 00:21:20,612
[somber music continues]

381
00:21:21,321 --> 00:21:24,199
Sir, don't go any further.

382
00:21:24,283 --> 00:21:27,035
It's already flooded!
The water is too deep there.

383
00:21:27,119 --> 00:21:28,578
- Hang on…
- It's too risky.

384
00:21:28,662 --> 00:21:30,914
There are live electrical wires
hanging loose.

385
00:21:30,998 --> 00:21:31,957
But I'm still looking for someone.

386
00:21:32,040 --> 00:21:33,542
- Ibyang! Someone needs to help that child!
- There's Ibyang!

387
00:21:33,625 --> 00:21:35,544
- Do you know her?
- [woman] She's on the roof of a house!

388
00:21:35,627 --> 00:21:36,586
There she is! Ibyang!

389
00:21:36,670 --> 00:21:38,755
[Ibyang] Help!

390
00:21:39,965 --> 00:21:41,550
Help!

391
00:21:41,633 --> 00:21:43,677
- [power line crashes]
- [speaks indistinctly]

392
00:21:44,261 --> 00:21:46,430
Go call the town guards for help!

393
00:21:47,222 --> 00:21:48,390
Help!

394
00:21:48,473 --> 00:21:50,309
[tense music playing]

395
00:21:50,392 --> 00:21:52,185
[woman] Please help the poor child. Hurry!

396
00:21:52,269 --> 00:21:53,562
Help!

397
00:21:53,645 --> 00:21:56,523
- [brooding music playing]
- [sobbing]

398
00:21:57,524 --> 00:22:00,986
- [thunder crashing]
- [power line sizzles]

399
00:22:01,611 --> 00:22:03,030
- [thunder crashing]
- Ibyang!

400
00:22:03,113 --> 00:22:05,824
- [power line sizzles]
- Help!

401
00:22:05,907 --> 00:22:07,951
[tense music continues]

402
00:22:08,035 --> 00:22:10,620
- [Ibyang] Help!
- [thunder crashing]

403
00:22:10,704 --> 00:22:12,372
[Ibyang sobbing]

404
00:22:13,415 --> 00:22:14,750
[Atoy] Ibyang.

405
00:22:14,833 --> 00:22:17,294
[Ibyang sobbing]

406
00:22:19,504 --> 00:22:22,090
[Atoy] Ibyang. Ibyang, come here.

407
00:22:22,174 --> 00:22:24,593
Don't worry. Come on.

408
00:22:25,427 --> 00:22:27,471
- Atoy?
- It's Atoy. I'm here. Come on.

409
00:22:27,554 --> 00:22:30,098
- I'll save you. Come on.
- But I'm scared.

410
00:22:30,182 --> 00:22:31,224
[Atoy] Ibyang, let's go.

411
00:22:31,308 --> 00:22:33,101
- [Ibyang] I'm scared.
- Just hold on to me.

412
00:22:33,185 --> 00:22:35,020
- Hold on to me, quickly. Come on.
- [sobbing]

413
00:22:35,604 --> 00:22:37,856
[Atoy] I'm here to save you.
Slowly, watch your step.

414
00:22:37,939 --> 00:22:39,107
- [Atoy] Okay.
- [sobbing]

415
00:22:39,191 --> 00:22:41,568
Watch your step. Let's go.

416
00:22:41,651 --> 00:22:43,236
- Okay…
- [sobbing]

417
00:22:43,320 --> 00:22:48,158
- [power line sizzles]
- [sobbing]

418
00:22:48,241 --> 00:22:51,161
[stirring music playing]

419
00:22:51,244 --> 00:22:56,249
- [sobbing]
- [thunder crashing]

420
00:22:59,836 --> 00:23:01,213
[Atoy] Just hold on. Hold on.

421
00:23:01,296 --> 00:23:04,382
- [sobbing]
- [stirring music continues]

422
00:23:05,008 --> 00:23:06,384
[sobs]

423
00:23:09,679 --> 00:23:11,473
[thunder crashes]

424
00:23:11,556 --> 00:23:13,642
- Oh, oh. Come inside.
- [Atoy] Miss Cita.

425
00:23:14,142 --> 00:23:15,977
I'm relieved you came back for Ibyang.

426
00:23:16,937 --> 00:23:18,230
- [Atoy grunts]
- All right.

427
00:23:18,313 --> 00:23:21,149
‪[Cita sighs] Go grab a towel. Okay.

428
00:23:23,485 --> 00:23:25,487
My goodness, are you all right?

429
00:23:26,321 --> 00:23:28,240
- [Atoy] Hey, hey, hey. Here, here, here
- Oh, my. Hand it over. Give it to me.

430
00:23:28,323 --> 00:23:30,158
- My goodness.
- [somber music playing]

431
00:23:30,242 --> 00:23:32,119
- [thunder crashing]
- [Ibyang whimpers]

432
00:23:32,202 --> 00:23:33,537
Oh, my. Watch her back. Watch it.

433
00:23:33,620 --> 00:23:37,958
Thank you, Miss Cita.
Thank you, Master Cutter.

434
00:23:38,041 --> 00:23:40,794
What were you even doing on top of a bus?

435
00:23:40,877 --> 00:23:43,088
You should be staying at home,

436
00:23:43,171 --> 00:23:45,298
not wandering around everywhere.

437
00:23:45,382 --> 00:23:47,050
I can't believe
you got caught in the rain.

438
00:23:47,134 --> 00:23:50,387
I lived inside that old bus.

439
00:23:50,470 --> 00:23:52,889
My sister, Ame, and I are homeless.

440
00:24:00,188 --> 00:24:03,650
[somber music continues]

441
00:24:05,777 --> 00:24:09,197
I secured this,
so I could return it to you.

442
00:24:09,281 --> 00:24:13,201
I was hoping you'd agree
to help me find my sister, Ame.

443
00:24:14,244 --> 00:24:17,622
Oh, I'm sorry.
I'll just dry it off instead.

444
00:24:17,706 --> 00:24:18,832
Give it to me. You don't
have to do that anymore.

445
00:24:19,749 --> 00:24:20,750
We're good now.

446
00:24:20,834 --> 00:24:23,378
[rain splattering]

447
00:24:25,881 --> 00:24:30,635
To be honest,
I would've helped you right away

448
00:24:31,511 --> 00:24:34,222
if you had just said the magic word.

449
00:24:34,306 --> 00:24:35,807
What magic word?

450
00:24:36,391 --> 00:24:37,517
Just "please."

451
00:24:37,601 --> 00:24:40,187
That's two words.

452
00:24:40,270 --> 00:24:43,023
You're already shivering, and yet you
still have the energy to be sarcastic.

453
00:24:43,106 --> 00:24:49,779
Atoy, please help me find my sister, Ame.

454
00:24:49,863 --> 00:24:51,489
Please.

455
00:24:53,491 --> 00:24:55,452
Get her a new set of clothes.

456
00:24:55,535 --> 00:24:57,871
- [speaks indistinctly] Okay. Fine.
- Please hurry.

457
00:24:57,954 --> 00:24:59,039
[Cita whispers]

458
00:25:06,838 --> 00:25:10,967
[sentimental music playing]

459
00:25:16,514 --> 00:25:18,767
[Cita] I think the shirt fits you well.

460
00:25:18,850 --> 00:25:22,062
It's time for us to eat.
You must be starving.

461
00:25:22,145 --> 00:25:24,648
My goodness.

462
00:25:28,068 --> 00:25:29,778
[utensils clinking]

463
00:25:29,861 --> 00:25:31,363
[sentimental music continues]

464
00:25:31,446 --> 00:25:33,490
Take it easy.

465
00:25:33,573 --> 00:25:37,869
[sentimental music continues]

466
00:26:01,685 --> 00:26:03,019
- [Atoy] Miss Cita.
- Mmm?

467
00:26:03,103 --> 00:26:05,522
Thank you for looking after that child.

468
00:26:07,857 --> 00:26:11,111
I'll buy new clothes for her tomorrow.

469
00:26:12,612 --> 00:26:15,907
Anyway, how are you doing? Are you okay?

470
00:26:15,991 --> 00:26:17,492
You went through the flood.
Tthat was dangerous.

471
00:26:18,451 --> 00:26:20,870
It really felt like I was risking my life.

472
00:26:21,454 --> 00:26:26,251
Come to think of it, I could've died
from that sparking electric post.

473
00:26:26,334 --> 00:26:29,129
If not that, then leptospirosis.

474
00:26:29,212 --> 00:26:33,300
Or the stress from those
poorly done flood control projects.

475
00:26:34,384 --> 00:26:36,886
There's medicine for leptospirosis
available at the health center.

476
00:26:36,970 --> 00:26:38,513
You should get some.

477
00:26:38,596 --> 00:26:39,723
Mmm-hmm.

478
00:26:39,806 --> 00:26:42,267
[pensive music continues]

479
00:26:43,226 --> 00:26:44,436
[Atoy] All right.

480
00:26:44,936 --> 00:26:48,148
I hope I can finally get some good rest.
I hope you get some good sleep too.

481
00:26:49,149 --> 00:26:52,027
That Ibyang really caused
a lot of trouble.

482
00:26:52,110 --> 00:26:56,197
But you still chose to save her.

483
00:26:56,281 --> 00:26:57,741
And that's what matters.

484
00:26:58,950 --> 00:27:00,035
I'll go ahead now.

485
00:27:01,995 --> 00:27:03,455
- Please take care.
- Okay.

486
00:27:04,664 --> 00:27:09,836
[gentle music playing]

487
00:27:14,466 --> 00:27:18,094
[chain clanking]

488
00:27:19,262 --> 00:27:24,017
[gentle music playing]

489
00:27:32,609 --> 00:27:37,155
[gentle music playing]

490
00:27:47,624 --> 00:27:52,629
[whimpering]

491
00:28:00,720 --> 00:28:04,724
Ame, where are you?

492
00:28:05,600 --> 00:28:07,727
[sobs] Please come back.

493
00:28:08,520 --> 00:28:12,023
[gentle music playing]

494
00:28:12,107 --> 00:28:13,233
Ibyang.

495
00:28:15,068 --> 00:28:16,027
[sobs]

496
00:28:16,111 --> 00:28:18,530
Don't worry. We'll look for your sister.

497
00:28:28,706 --> 00:28:33,086
[gentle music continues]

498
00:28:51,354 --> 00:28:55,108
[stirring music playing]

499
00:28:55,191 --> 00:28:57,277
[electronic blipping]

500
00:28:57,360 --> 00:29:02,031
[suspenseful music playing]

501
00:29:05,285 --> 00:29:07,829
[Andot] <i>Guys, let's do a good job.</i>
We don't have the money to pay those guys.

502
00:29:07,912 --> 00:29:09,122
[Jason, in English]
<i>We can't lose this game, Gavin.</i>

503
00:29:09,205 --> 00:29:10,039
- [Gavin, in English] <i>Don't worry, Jason.</i>
- Putoy is open!

504
00:29:10,123 --> 00:29:11,875
- [Gavin] <i>I'll guard the girl.</i>
- Hurry up!

505
00:29:13,209 --> 00:29:14,127
[players exclaim]

506
00:29:14,210 --> 00:29:15,837
[in English] <i>Last game. Winner takes all.</i>

507
00:29:15,920 --> 00:29:17,172
[Karla] <i>I'm going for 3.</i>

508
00:29:17,255 --> 00:29:19,841
<i>If I miss, I'll cover the bet myself.</i>

509
00:29:19,924 --> 00:29:22,010
- [Karla laughs] Oh!
- [players whooping]

510
00:29:22,093 --> 00:29:25,013
[overlapping chatter]

511
00:29:25,096 --> 00:29:27,056
[Ibyang] <i>Magic inside that place?</i>

512
00:29:27,140 --> 00:29:32,604
Why would Miss Bebang take my sister
into a place full of sexy girls?

513
00:29:32,687 --> 00:29:35,106
You won't be able to get
out of here anymore, you witch!

514
00:29:35,190 --> 00:29:37,317
Get that inside your thick skull,

515
00:29:37,400 --> 00:29:39,360
- so you don't drag us down with you!
- [Ame] Ouch! It hurts!

516
00:29:39,444 --> 00:29:40,612
[in English] I want him banned here!

517
00:29:40,695 --> 00:29:43,740
[Lorna] <i>Yes, Sir Red.</i>
<i>He's banned from coming here.</i>

518
00:29:43,823 --> 00:29:46,951
- [thudding]
- [grunting]

519
00:29:47,035 --> 00:29:49,579
[Ibyang] <i>Looks like no one's coming</i>
<i>to save you, Ame.</i>

520
00:29:49,662 --> 00:29:51,039
<i>So I'll do it myself instead.</i>

521
00:29:52,957 --> 00:29:54,334
Jeffrey Matulac?

522
00:29:54,417 --> 00:29:55,376
[Jeffrey] <i>Boss.</i>

523
00:29:56,211 --> 00:29:57,086
[in English] Present, ma'am.

524
00:29:57,170 --> 00:29:59,631
[stirring music playing]

525
00:30:02,509 --> 00:30:04,719
Subtitle translation by:
Inocencio Cañete Raman Jr.
